I'm sorry for not responding sooner to your email below - unfortunately I lost it in the backlog after the summer holidays.

What you say is interesting, and suggests that you're focusing on using soil moisture measurements to improve the service. How do you envisage this working in practice? Would an insurance product only be offered to a farmer if the soil moisture on the farm could be measured?

